So this first map, this
is roughly from the

00:05:39.724 --> 00:05:42.974
third century BCE and third century BCE

00:05:44.385 --> 00:05:47.262
you might remember Rome is
a republic at this time,

00:05:47.262 --> 00:05:51.417
but it's not the dominant
power in the Mediterranean.

00:05:51.417 --> 00:05:53.665
Just to give ourselves some bearings,

00:05:53.665 --> 00:05:58.283
you might remember that in
the later fourth century BCE

00:05:58.283 --> 00:06:01.586
that's when Alexander conquers much of,

00:06:01.586 --> 00:06:05.289
or most of Greece, Macedonia,
the Persian Empire.

00:06:05.289 --> 00:06:08.519
Which included at the time Egypt,

00:06:08.519 --> 00:06:11.260
and as we get into the third century BCE,

00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:15.154
you still have the fragments
of Alexanders empire,

00:06:15.154 --> 00:06:18.094
but these are still significant
powers in the regions.

00:06:18.094 --> 00:06:20.546
You also have the Carthaginian Empire.

00:06:20.546 --> 00:06:22.644
Which you see here in blue in North Africa

00:06:22.644 --> 00:06:24.269
and southern Spain,

00:06:24.269 --> 00:06:26.975
and this period you have a series of wars

00:06:26.975 --> 00:06:29.734
between the Romans and the Carthaginians

00:06:29.734 --> 00:06:31.166
known as the Punic Wars,

00:06:31.166 --> 00:06:33.534
and we'll do videos in
depth on the Punic Wars.

00:06:33.534 --> 00:06:35.072
They're called the Punic Wars

00:06:35.072 --> 00:06:37.086
because the term Punic, it comes from

00:06:37.086 --> 00:06:39.017
what the Romans called the Phoenicians,

00:06:39.017 --> 00:06:41.911
and Carthage was actually settled,

00:06:41.911 --> 00:06:43.668
founded by ancient Phoenicians.

00:06:43.668 --> 00:06:46.277
So you can kinda consider
this the Phoenician War

00:06:46.277 --> 00:06:48.925
or the descendants of the Phoenician Wars,

00:06:48.925 --> 00:06:51.827
but that's why it's called Punic,

00:06:51.827 --> 00:06:55.628
but the Romans eventually
win the multiple rounds

00:06:55.628 --> 00:06:57.837
of Punic Wars, take over their territory,

00:06:57.837 --> 00:07:00.234
and eventually destroy Carthage.

00:07:00.234 --> 00:07:02.984
Carthage is destroyed in 146 BCE,

00:07:04.016 --> 00:07:07.375
and we'll talk about that in more detail.

00:07:07.375 --> 00:07:11.369
Now as we go into the first century BCE,

00:07:11.369 --> 00:07:16.175
this is when Rome goes form
being a republic to an empire,

00:07:16.175 --> 00:07:19.998
and it happens when the
general, Julius Caesar,

00:07:19.998 --> 00:07:24.614
he's able to conquer Gaul
for the Roman Republic.

00:07:24.614 --> 00:07:26.947
So Gaul is modern day France

00:07:28.048 --> 00:07:30.554
and some other surrounding regions,

00:07:30.554 --> 00:07:35.429
and he is so powerful that
when he comes back to Rome,

00:07:35.429 --> 00:07:39.410
a civil war ensues and
Julius Caesar is able to

00:07:39.410 --> 00:07:41.225
essentially win the civil war,

00:07:41.225 --> 00:07:43.459
declare himself a dictator,

00:07:43.459 --> 00:07:47.338
and then his adopted son
Augustus, right over here,

00:07:47.338 --> 00:07:49.838
is in 27 BCE declared Emperor,

00:07:51.992 --> 00:07:55.341
and that's the beginning
of the Roman Empire,

00:07:55.341 --> 00:07:57.685
and we keep going, and I
think I've already mentioned

00:07:57.685 --> 00:07:59.036
it once in this video,

00:07:59.036 --> 00:08:03.953
but eventually we get a split
in the fourth century CE

00:08:03.953 --> 00:08:06.137
where we have eastern and western halves

00:08:06.137 --> 00:08:07.566
of the Roman Empire.

00:08:07.566 --> 00:08:10.621
The western side centered at Rome,

00:08:10.621 --> 00:08:14.756
the eastern side centered at
what was originally Byzantium,

00:08:14.756 --> 00:08:18.609
renamed Constantinople,
and today Istanbul,

00:08:18.609 --> 00:08:20.831
and as we get into the fifth century,

00:08:20.831 --> 00:08:22.357
that's when the western empire

00:08:22.357 --> 00:08:24.362
especially starts to
really go into decline

00:08:24.362 --> 00:08:27.270
and is eventually sacked in 476,

00:08:27.270 --> 00:08:30.437
but the eastern empire keeps on going.

